This is a subpage of CategoryModes. It lists multimedia modes to listen to music or view images.
But see MusicPlayers.

* AbcMode -- The music file format
* ArtistMode -- ASCII art including with the mouse
* AutoImageFileMode -- View images in Emacs
* DocViewMode -- View documents (PDF/PS/DVI) inside Emacs
* EmacsCsound -- Mode for editing Csound files
* EmacsImageManipulation -- mogrify images with imagemagick
* EmacsPhotoDatabase -- manage film, negative, and print information (silver-based photography)
* EmacsSuperCollider -- Develop synthetic audio
* ImageMode -- new in Emacs 22
** [http://user42.tuxfamily.org/imagetext/index.html imagetext.el] -- view text comments from PNG etc in ImageMode and AutoImageFileMode
* JpegMode -- details of jpeg file internals
* LookMode -- opens a list of files in a temporary, writable buffer.  Allows safe resizing of images with EmacsImageManipulation mode.
* MusicPlayers -- play CDs and MP3s in your favourite editor
* [[Processing]] -- mode for editing, running, compiling (etc.) Processing <code>.pde</code> files
* PictureMode -- ASCII art
* ThumbsMode -- image browsing
* [[Tumme]] -- image browsing
* EmacsImageViewer -- A simple image viewer.
* EMMS - Emacs Multi-Media System, an application to play multimedia files from Emacs using external players

----
